ca.mcgill.ecse211.finalproject.controller

Class RiverTraversal

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.mcgill.ecse211.finalproject.controller.RiverTraversal

  • public class RiverTraversal
extends java.lang.Object
    Responsible for finding a path through shallow water and actual traversal of river using shallow water crossing. This class mainly contains the doTrversal method which takes care of this river traversal to go to the green side.

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void doTraversal()
      Method responsible for performing river traversal by first entering through middle of shallow water entry,
      traveling along this middle until one reaches midpoint of vertical segment's entry of shallow water,
      then traveling to exit of vertical segment of shallow water.
